Class Customer

  • java.lang.Object
    • Customer

  • public class Customer
extends java.lang.Object
    Object Customer represents table of online shop database. It is creating when we are going to add information of new customer to existing database. It contains data about customerId, name, surname, address and telephone number. Every input details should fit to certain format - otherwise program can not accept them.

    ***

    Customer class is used by Inscriber class to add new "customer insert" to "sql_dml.txt". It is also used by Tally class to add new object to ArrayList with every customers and to create chart with existing customerId (this chart is needful to set correct customerId in Order class.
    Version:
    2.0 15.03.2018
    Author:
    Magdalena Wisniewska

      • setCustomerDetails

        private void setCustomerDetails()
        setCustomerDetails method is used to call methods like setName(), setSurname() etc. to collect values of every variable essential to create new instance of Customer class . Next methods are calling till one of the variables (loading from user as Strings) equals "END". In this way new customer is not created and unique customerId which was booked for him can be reuse.
